Malta and Italy held candle-lit vigils in memory of the 900 migrants who died off Libya this weekend . 
  People lay candles by the sea in Valetta and Rome's Verano Cemetery to remember victims . 
  Three people died when a wooden boat ran aground on the Greek island of Rhodes . 
  Death toll from this year's Mediterranean migrant tragedy is now 1,800 . 
  Italy's coast guard rescued 220 migrants from two rubber boats off the coast of Sicily today . 
  Emergency meeting of EU leaders in Brussels will announce only 5,000 refugees will be granted safe haven in Europe . 
 